<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 245.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-03"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1865,</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 14th
                            instant, No. 169, predicting a favorable reception in Europe of the
                            intelligence of the withdrawal from the insurgents of the character of
                            belligerents by those governments which have accorded to them privileges
                            upon that ground. It is to be regretted that European maritime powers so
                            tamely yielded to slaveholders’ threats, and unnecessarily conceded a
                            belligerent character to the rebels. The evils which have resulted from
                            the concession are deplorable, but they are passed.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pike,</hi>
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>